506
00:59:42,880 --> 00:59:44,836
Prepare for reception.

507
00:59:45,640 --> 00:59:48,279
Radar blackout is now complete.

508
00:59:49,400 --> 00:59:52,198
Radar blackout is now complete.

509
01:00:09,120 --> 01:00:11,634
Moscow radio's already saying we did it.

510
01:00:11,760 --> 01:00:14,433
The president's called
a press conference for 2pm.

511
01:00:14,560 --> 01:00:16,835
He'll deny emphatically we were involved.

512
01:00:16,960 --> 01:00:18,916
- But can we prove it?
- Of course not.

513
01:00:19,040 --> 01:00:21,110
No one will believe the Russians did it.

514
01:00:21,240 --> 01:00:24,357
Now they'll use the excuse
to shoot down our next Jupiter.

515
01:00:24,480 --> 01:00:28,758
Houston to Washington. We followed him
for one orbit, now he's offthe screen.

516
01:00:28,880 --> 01:00:30,836
That means he's coming down.

517
01:00:30,960 --> 01:00:34,748
- Yeah, but where?
- Some place in Russia. It has to be.

518
01:00:35,480 --> 01:00:38,472
The British theory about Japan
is nonsense.

519
01:00:38,600 --> 01:00:40,556
- Forget Japan.
- I agree.

520
01:00:40,680 --> 01:00:43,911
We've re-photographed
every square inch.

521
01:01:17,560 --> 01:01:20,233
Ventilator fans to full power.

522
01:01:20,360 --> 01:01:22,316
Open all air ducts.

523
01:01:22,440 --> 01:01:24,396
Area safe to enter.

524
01:01:24,520 --> 01:01:26,476
All crews to stations.

525
01:01:26,600 --> 01:01:28,716
All air ducts to normal.

526
01:01:30,480 --> 01:01:32,436
Air ducts opened.

527
01:01:32,560 --> 01:01:34,630
- Close crater.
- Closing crater.

528
01:01:35,600 --> 01:01:37,556
Fire guards to station.

529
01:01:48,320 --> 01:01:51,437
Ventilator fans to normal. Open shutters.

530
01:01:53,920 --> 01:01:55,876
Reception complete.

531
01:01:58,000 --> 01:02:00,275
Withdraw captive spaceship.

532
01:02:03,360 --> 01:02:05,316
Guards to stations.

533
01:02:34,400 --> 01:02:37,437
Remove the prisoners.

534
01:02:58,480 --> 01:03:00,914
I shall be in my apartment.

535
01:03:01,920 --> 01:03:04,070
I may send for you later.

536
01:03:30,880 --> 01:03:34,395
I must congratulate you, gentlemen,
upon your superb equipment.

537
01:03:34,520 --> 01:03:37,353
We congratulate you, sir,
upon the way you handle it.

538
01:03:37,480 --> 01:03:40,631
Our clients are satisfied
with the progress so far?

539
01:03:40,760 --> 01:03:44,070
- My government is quite satisfied.
- Good.

540
01:03:44,200 --> 01:03:45,679
Hans!

541
01:03:50,200 --> 01:03:53,636
You will see that my piranha fish
get very hungry.

542
01:03:54,520 --> 01:03:58,308
They can strip a man to the bone
in 30 seconds.

543
01:04:09,480 --> 01:04:12,756
I have decided to ask for
a little money in advance.

544
01:04:12,880 --> 01:04:17,032
I want the sum of 100 million dollars,
in gold bullion,

545
01:04:17,160 --> 01:04:19,674
deposited in our account in Buenos Aires.

546
01:04:19,800 --> 01:04:22,189
Our agreement states
no money should be paid

547
01:04:22,320 --> 01:04:25,710
until war has broken out
between Russia and the United States.

548
01:04:25,840 --> 01:04:29,833
- This is extortion.
- Extortion is my business.

549
01:04:29,960 --> 01:04:32,315
Go and think it over, gentlemen. I'm busy.

550
01:04:33,240 --> 01:04:36,312
Osato and Number 1 1 , report now.

551
01:04:50,560 --> 01:04:53,597
An unknown Englishman
was in your office the other day.

552
01:04:53,720 --> 01:04:55,551
Correct, Number One.

553
01:04:55,680 --> 01:04:58,513
- Do you know what gun this is?
- Walther PPK.

554
01:04:59,480 --> 01:05:02,597
Only one person we know
uses this sort of gun.

555
01:05:03,640 --> 01:05:05,790
James Bond.

556
01:05:06,280 --> 01:05:09,352
- But Bond is dead.
- It was in all the newspapers.

557
01:05:09,480 --> 01:05:10,754
Rubbish.

558
01:05:10,880 --> 01:05:12,791
Bond is alive.

559
01:05:12,920 --> 01:05:15,150
Unless you killed him, Mr Osato?

560
01:05:16,360 --> 01:05:18,316
Don't tell me you let him go.

561
01:05:18,760 --> 01:05:21,797
I gave Number 1 1
the strictest orders to eliminate him.

562
01:05:21,920 --> 01:05:23,672
And did she?

563
01:05:23,800 --> 01:05:25,836
She failed.

564
01:05:25,960 --> 01:05:29,157
You should have killed him.
You had plenty of opportunity.

565
01:05:29,280 --> 01:05:31,953
This organisation
does not tolerate failure.

566
01:05:32,080 --> 01:05:34,878
- I know, but you see, l...
- Go!

567
01:05:37,080 --> 01:05:38,354
Well?

568
01:05:46,680 --> 01:05:49,035
Osato!

569
01:05:57,880 --> 01:06:00,235
Kill Bond! Now!

570
01:06:00,880 --> 01:06:03,269
Yes, Number One. Yes. Yes, yes.

571
01:06:41,880 --> 01:06:44,440
- Hello.
- Bad news from outer space.

572
01:06:44,560 --> 01:06:48,030
Yes, I heard it. Now the Russians
are accusing the Americans.

573
01:06:48,160 --> 01:06:50,196
Next time it will be war.

574
01:06:50,320 --> 01:06:53,118
- We'll have to get down to the volcanoes.
- I agree.

575
01:06:53,240 --> 01:06:56,198
We'll also need
a company of first-rate men.

576
01:06:56,320 --> 01:06:58,390
Do you have any commandos here?

577
01:06:58,520 --> 01:07:00,476
I have much, much better.

578
01:07:00,960 --> 01:07:03,269
Ninjas. Top-secret, Bond-san.

579
01:07:04,160 --> 01:07:06,116
This is my ninja training school.

580
01:07:12,720 --> 01:07:15,951
- Ninjas?
- The art of concealment and surprise.

581
01:07:50,480 --> 01:07:52,835
This must develop
very fast reflex actions.

582
01:07:52,960 --> 01:07:54,632
And spiritual strength.

583
01:08:26,280 --> 01:08:29,158
Now, we will see some modern ninjas.

584
01:08:32,560 --> 01:08:34,516
My plan is this.

585
01:08:34,640 --> 01:08:36,596
I make a base on the Ama island.

586
01:08:36,720 --> 01:08:39,075
100 of my ninjas will slide in unseen.

587
01:08:39,800 --> 01:08:41,995
They will be workers and fishermen.

588
01:08:42,120 --> 01:08:44,076
- What about me?
- Later.

589
01:08:44,200 --> 01:08:47,510
But for the moment,
these will interest you. Rocket guns.

590
01:08:47,640 --> 01:08:49,198
Very powerful.

591
01:08:49,320 --> 01:08:51,754
See the holes in the back
for jet propulsion.

592
01:08:55,160 --> 01:08:57,720
- It's a fine gun.
- All rocket guns.

593
01:08:59,360 --> 01:09:01,396
This is our special baby rocket.

594
01:09:02,720 --> 01:09:06,030
Very useful for people who smoke
too many cigarettes, like you.

595
01:09:13,000 --> 01:09:15,798
- Accurate up to 30 yards.
- Very neat.

596
01:09:15,920 --> 01:09:19,276
- It can save your life.
- You sound like a commercial.

597
01:09:20,800 --> 01:09:24,031
- What's the plan for me?
- First, you become a Japanese.

598
01:09:24,160 --> 01:09:26,390
Second, you train hard and quickly

599
01:09:26,520 --> 01:09:28,829
to become a ninja like us.

600
01:09:29,360 --> 01:09:32,750
And third, to give you extra-special cover,

601
01:09:32,880 --> 01:09:34,836
you take a wife.

602
01:09:43,080 --> 01:09:44,957
Regretfully impossible.

603
01:09:45,080 --> 01:09:46,832
You must marry Ama girl.

604
01:09:46,960 --> 01:09:48,951
One who is known on the island.

605
01:09:49,080 --> 01:09:52,277
- Is she pretty?
- She has a face like a pig.

606
01:09:52,400 --> 01:09:55,676
- To hell with that idea.
- But this is duty.

607
01:09:57,760 --> 01:10:00,194
The girl I have chosen
is an agent of mine.

608
01:10:00,320 --> 01:10:02,629
But first, you must become Japanese.

609
01:10:07,600 --> 01:10:10,353
Eyepieces to Hera.

610
01:10:15,800 --> 01:10:17,995
Why don't you just
dye the parts that show?

611
01:10:27,560 --> 01:10:30,916
- Konbanwa.
- Konbanwa.

612
01:10:36,480 --> 01:10:39,040
Tiger said, from now on,

613
01:10:39,160 --> 01:10:41,958
you must do everything Japanese-style.

614
01:10:42,080 --> 01:10:43,991
Everything?

615
01:10:44,120 --> 01:10:46,076
Good for Tiger.

616
01:12:45,720 --> 01:12:47,199
I'm...

617
01:12:49,560 --> 01:12:51,790
I... I...

618
01:12:51,920 --> 01:12:52,909
Aki!

619
01:12:53,040 --> 01:12:54,996
I'm...

620
01:13:03,320 --> 01:13:05,276
She's dead.

621
01:13:06,320 --> 01:13:08,276
Poisoned.

622
01:13:11,680 --> 01:13:13,830
Tiger, we must get to that island.

623
01:13:13,960 --> 01:13:17,111
You're almost ready.
Just two more days' training.

624
01:13:56,520 --> 01:13:59,671
- You killed him.
- Yeah, he tried to kill me.

625
01:14:03,040 --> 01:14:04,996
This man is a stranger from outside.

626
01:14:06,880 --> 01:14:09,030
It's lucky we're getting out of here.

627
01:14:09,160 --> 01:14:12,835
Tomorrow you will be a poor Japanese
worker, with humble Japanese wife.

628
01:14:12,960 --> 01:14:14,916
Yeah, with a face like a pig.

629
01:17:39,040 --> 01:17:40,996
My men are already ashore.

630
01:17:41,120 --> 01:17:43,076
All over the island.

631
01:17:43,200 --> 01:17:46,795
We have four days left.
It is not much time.

632
01:18:45,760 --> 01:18:47,716
This is my house.

633
01:18:50,200 --> 01:18:52,634
My friend has made us some food.

634
01:18:54,640 --> 01:18:56,596
Do you live here alone?

635
01:18:56,720 --> 01:18:59,234
Yes. My parents are dead.

636
01:18:59,360 --> 01:19:01,316
Sit down, please.

637
01:19:03,400 --> 01:19:04,913
Oysters.

638
01:19:05,040 --> 01:19:07,554
Is this the only room there is?

639
01:19:07,680 --> 01:19:09,352
Yes.

640
01:19:09,480 --> 01:19:11,436
That is your bed.

641
01:19:11,560 --> 01:19:13,516
I shall sleep over there.

642
01:19:15,080 --> 01:19:18,072
- We're supposed to be married.
- Think again, please.

643
01:19:18,200 --> 01:19:20,156
You gave false name to priest.

644
01:19:20,280 --> 01:19:23,352
But we must keep up appearances!
We're on our honeymoon.

645
01:19:23,480 --> 01:19:25,869
No honeymoon. This is business.

646
01:19:30,280 --> 01:19:32,430
I won't need these.

647
01:20:00,760 --> 01:20:03,194
- Bond-san.
- What's wrong?

648
01:20:03,880 --> 01:20:06,553
The Americans have changed
the launching date.

649
01:20:06,680 --> 01:20:08,636
The countdown has already started.

650
01:20:08,760 --> 01:20:11,718
The president has given
a last warning to the Russians.

651
01:20:11,840 --> 01:20:14,354
- When does it go up?
- Tonight, midnight. Our time.

652
01:20:14,480 --> 01:20:18,075
- Did your men search the island?
- Yes. There is nothing but volcanoes.

653
01:20:18,200 --> 01:20:20,156
Everything is so normal around here.

654
01:20:20,280 --> 01:20:22,475
- Nothing happens.
- One thing has happened.

655
01:20:22,600 --> 01:20:25,592
Yesterday an Ama girl
rowed her boat into Ryuzaki.

656
01:20:25,720 --> 01:20:28,234
- Ryuzaki?
- It is a big cave on the mainland.

657
01:20:28,360 --> 01:20:30,669
And when her boat floated out again,

658
01:20:30,800 --> 01:20:32,552
she was dead.

659
01:20:34,440 --> 01:20:37,398
- Was that the funeral we saw yesterday?
- Yes.

660
01:20:37,520 --> 01:20:39,750
- How did she die?
- Nobody knows.

661
01:20:41,480 --> 01:20:43,436
- Can you take me to this cave?
- Yes.

662
01:20:43,560 --> 01:20:45,232
We'll slip away from the fishing fleet
in the morning.

663
01:21:25,960 --> 01:21:27,712
All right?

664
01:21:27,840 --> 01:21:29,796
Now, where is this cave?

665
01:21:29,920 --> 01:21:31,876
It's straight across.

666
01:21:32,000 --> 01:21:33,956
The cave is over there.

667
01:22:01,640 --> 01:22:03,596
Gas. Get over the side.

668
01:22:03,720 --> 01:22:04,994
Quick!

669
01:22:29,000 --> 01:22:32,037
Phosgene gas, to keep the visitors away.

670
01:22:32,720 --> 01:22:34,870
Did you notice the sulphur on the walls?

671
01:22:35,000 --> 01:22:36,956
- The yellow?
- Yes.

672
01:22:37,080 --> 01:22:40,197
It was once an underground outlet
for the volcanic lava.

673
01:22:40,320 --> 01:22:43,835
- There must be a long tunnel.
- Miles of it.

674
01:22:43,960 --> 01:22:46,190
It leads all the way,

675
01:22:46,320 --> 01:22:47,753
right up to the top.

676
01:22:47,880 --> 01:22:50,075
That's where we have to go.
Can you make it?

677
01:22:50,200 --> 01:22:52,760
Of course. It's business.

678
01:22:52,880 --> 01:22:54,233
Good.

679
01:23:11,680 --> 01:23:13,636
May I rest a moment?

680
01:23:13,760 --> 01:23:15,716
Surely.

681
01:23:18,880 --> 01:23:20,836
It's hard work.

682
01:23:22,280 --> 01:23:23,838
Some honeymoon!

683
01:23:50,920 --> 01:23:54,037
It's going down! lnto the volcano!

684
01:23:58,800 --> 01:24:00,995
Heliport to position.

685
01:24:03,120 --> 01:24:05,429
The honeymoon's over. Come on.

686
01:24:39,720 --> 01:24:42,234
This volcano isn't active, is it?

687
01:24:42,360 --> 01:24:44,590
It never has been. Not in my lifetime.

688
01:24:44,720 --> 01:24:47,712
There's been some
terrific heat here recently.

689
01:24:47,840 --> 01:24:49,831
What happened to the helicopter?

690
01:24:49,960 --> 01:24:51,916
It's down there somewhere.

691
01:24:52,800 --> 01:24:54,756
Come on.

692
01:24:56,800 --> 01:24:58,711
Stand by. Mark.

693
01:24:58,840 --> 01:25:00,910
Stand by for ten-second countdown.

694
01:25:01,040 --> 01:25:02,758
10, 9, 8...

695
01:25:02,880 --> 01:25:05,553
All units worldwide
will remain at readiness

696
01:25:05,680 --> 01:25:07,830
so long as the spacecraft is in orbit.

697
01:25:08,000 --> 01:25:09,991
..3, 2, 1.

698
01:25:11,800 --> 01:25:13,756
Ignition.

699
01:25:23,880 --> 01:25:26,997
This is it, gentlemen.
All we can do now is wait and pray.

700
01:25:47,440 --> 01:25:49,237
Is that deep?

701
01:25:49,360 --> 01:25:51,316
They usually are - very.

702
01:25:55,800 --> 01:25:57,677
It's metal!

703
01:25:57,800 --> 01:25:59,756
Wait here.

704
01:26:13,480 --> 01:26:15,994
Heliport to takeoffposition.

705
01:26:22,240 --> 01:26:23,878
Open crater.

706
01:26:41,880 --> 01:26:43,677
Emergency crews to stations.

707
01:26:46,360 --> 01:26:49,352
Go to Tanaka.
Tell him to come with every man he's got.

708
01:26:49,480 --> 01:26:50,595
Yes.

709
01:27:22,720 --> 01:27:25,234
Heliport to standbyposition.

710
01:28:05,880 --> 01:28:08,269
Astronauts to dressing rooms.

711
01:28:09,120 --> 01:28:11,076
Astronauts to dressing rooms.

712
01:28:21,080 --> 01:28:22,832
Attention, attention.

713
01:28:22,960 --> 01:28:26,316
American target vehicle is now in orbit.

714
01:28:27,200 --> 01:28:30,237
Interception will take place
in two hours' time.

715
01:28:44,560 --> 01:28:46,516
Washington, this is Houston.

716
01:28:46,640 --> 01:28:48,596
Houston to Washington.

717
01:28:49,280 --> 01:28:52,955
Our vehicle is now
120 nautical miles altitude,

718
01:28:53,640 --> 01:28:56,234
170 miles downrange.

719
01:28:59,320 --> 01:29:02,471
Jupiter to Houston,
we now have second phase.

720
01:29:02,600 --> 01:29:04,511
Roger, Jupiter.

721
01:29:04,640 --> 01:29:07,518
Four hours 36 minutes into the mission.

722
01:29:07,640 --> 01:29:10,234
- Can you give us a time?
- Roger.

723
01:29:13,760 --> 01:29:15,716
Connect igniter cable.

724
01:29:17,160 --> 01:29:19,276
Connect igniter cable.

725
01:29:44,560 --> 01:29:47,279
Radar technicians, report to control room.

726
01:29:48,360 --> 01:29:51,397
Radar technicians, report to control room.

727
01:30:09,760 --> 01:30:12,593
T minus 100 minutes and counting.

728
01:30:13,800 --> 01:30:16,678
Did you volunteer for astronaut training?

729
01:30:16,800 --> 01:30:19,837
In our country, we say cosmonaut.
Yes, both of us...

730
01:30:22,280 --> 01:30:24,953
Yes, since six months we started training.

731
01:30:25,960 --> 01:30:27,837
Good evening.

732
01:30:27,960 --> 01:30:29,757
Who the hell are you?

733
01:30:29,880 --> 01:30:32,235
Stand back, I'm gonna blow the lock.

734
01:30:39,320 --> 01:30:41,356
Stand back.

735
01:30:50,480 --> 01:30:52,436
Get into their uniforms.

736
01:31:52,360 --> 01:31:54,590
Astronauts have two minutes.

737
01:31:54,720 --> 01:31:56,676
Repeat, two minutes.

738
01:32:03,240 --> 01:32:06,152
Reserve astronaut to stand by.

739
01:32:08,680 --> 01:32:11,638
- Lock on target.
- Lock on target vehicle.

740
01:32:11,760 --> 01:32:13,910
Check secondary guidance.

741
01:32:14,040 --> 01:32:18,431
Launch time is now
T minus 90 minutes and counting.

742
01:32:18,560 --> 01:32:20,949
Astronauts to launching pad.

743
01:32:21,080 --> 01:32:23,150
Astronauts to launching pad.

744
01:32:24,200 --> 01:32:27,829
Repeat, astronauts
to launching pad immediately.

745
01:33:05,480 --> 01:33:08,199
Crews, stand by on gantry.

746
01:33:09,200 --> 01:33:11,031
Crews, stand by on gantry.

747
01:33:44,360 --> 01:33:48,114
- Stop that astronaut. Bring him to me.
- Stop that astronaut!

748
01:33:48,240 --> 01:33:51,596
- Summon the reserve astronaut!
- Reserve astronaut!

749
01:33:51,720 --> 01:33:55,349
Reserve astronaut
to launching pad, immediately.

750
01:34:03,880 --> 01:34:06,678
Re-coordinate with target vehicle.

751
01:34:06,800 --> 01:34:08,028
A new update

752
01:34:08,160 --> 01:34:12,472
with target vehicle
has been received from computers.

753
01:34:13,960 --> 01:34:17,999
We now have T minus seven minutes
and counting.

754
01:34:18,120 --> 01:34:20,554
You made a mistake, my friend.

755
01:34:20,680 --> 01:34:23,717
No astronaut enters the capsule
with his air conditioner.

756
01:34:23,840 --> 01:34:25,512
Remove his helmet!

757
01:34:30,880 --> 01:34:32,836
James Bond.

758
01:34:34,040 --> 01:34:36,600
Allow me to introduce myself.

759
01:34:38,000 --> 01:34:40,833
I am Ernst Stavro Blofeld.

760
01:34:41,960 --> 01:34:44,713
They told me
you were assassinated in Hong Kong.

761
01:34:45,400 --> 01:34:47,356
Yes, this is my second life.

762
01:34:49,400 --> 01:34:51,516
You only live twice, Mr Bond.

763
01:34:51,640 --> 01:34:54,200
Target vehicle
passing over central Russia.

764
01:34:54,320 --> 01:34:56,356
Approaching Mongolia.

765
01:34:56,480 --> 01:34:59,119
Track is as predicted. All computers...

766
01:34:59,240 --> 01:35:02,437
As you see,
I am about to inaugurate a little war.

767
01:35:02,560 --> 01:35:06,917
In a matter of hours, when America
and Russia have annihilated each other,

768
01:35:07,040 --> 01:35:09,679
we shall see a new power
dominating the world.

769
01:35:09,800 --> 01:35:13,873
- Target vehicle on scope.
- Brief check on target vehicle.

770
01:35:14,000 --> 01:35:16,514
Remove his suit and search him.

771
01:35:16,640 --> 01:35:19,632
Reserve astronaut ready on Bird 1.

772
01:35:29,040 --> 01:35:30,314
Prepare for firing.

773
01:35:30,440 --> 01:35:32,396
Clear the area.

774
01:35:33,400 --> 01:35:35,356
Clear the area.

775
01:35:37,560 --> 01:35:39,949
Emergency services to stand by.

776
01:35:40,920 --> 01:35:42,876
Area now clear.

777
01:35:46,320 --> 01:35:49,835
T minus one minute,
30 seconds and counting.

778
01:35:50,440 --> 01:35:53,113
Re-coordinate with target vehicle.

779
01:35:53,240 --> 01:35:55,196
Bird 1 now in readiness.

780
01:35:55,920 --> 01:35:59,196
Astronauts ready on Bird.
All systems are go.

781
01:35:59,320 --> 01:36:02,278
Close shutters.

782
01:36:03,360 --> 01:36:06,352
- Radar blackout commence.
- Radar blackout in operation.

783
01:36:09,680 --> 01:36:12,240
Effective range, kilometres 800.

784
01:36:12,360 --> 01:36:15,193
- Open crater.
- Opening crater.

785
01:36:17,680 --> 01:36:19,636
Crater opening.

786
01:36:19,760 --> 01:36:22,718
Bird 1 to liftoffposition.

787
01:36:40,040 --> 01:36:44,352
Gimbal the engines.
Pressurised tanks open.

788
01:36:44,480 --> 01:36:47,358
Ventilator fans to full power.

789
01:36:47,480 --> 01:36:48,595
10 seconds.

790
01:36:48,720 --> 01:36:50,517
9, 8,

791
01:36:50,640 --> 01:36:52,278
7, 6,

792
01:36:52,400 --> 01:36:54,277
5, 4,

793
01:36:54,400 --> 01:36:56,277
3, 2,

794
01:36:56,400 --> 01:36:58,231
1 , 0.

795
01:36:58,360 --> 01:37:00,590
Ignition.

796
01:37:25,280 --> 01:37:26,998
Close crater!

797
01:37:27,120 --> 01:37:29,076
Closing crater.

798
01:37:31,840 --> 01:37:34,229
Open shutters!

799
01:38:12,080 --> 01:38:14,275
Bird 1 to base. Separation complete.

800
01:38:14,400 --> 01:38:16,595
Confirm acquisition.

801
01:38:16,720 --> 01:38:18,870
Calling Bird 1.

802
01:38:19,000 --> 01:38:22,310
You are 70 nautical miles downrange.
200 miles altitude.

803
01:38:22,440 --> 01:38:25,432
Hans, our job will soon be done.

804
01:38:25,560 --> 01:38:29,872
Blow them up as soon as they have
captured the Americans. Here is the key

805
01:38:31,160 --> 01:38:33,355
to operate the exploder button.

806
01:38:33,480 --> 01:38:35,630
There are men in the crater!

807
01:38:37,200 --> 01:38:38,189
Crater guns, fire.

808
01:38:38,320 --> 01:38:40,276
Crater guns, open fire.

809
01:39:01,600 --> 01:39:03,750
The firing power inside my crater

810
01:39:03,880 --> 01:39:06,075
is enough to annihilate a small army.

811
01:39:06,880 --> 01:39:09,030
You can watch it all on TV.

812
01:39:09,160 --> 01:39:12,118
It's the last programme
you're likely to see.

813
01:39:12,240 --> 01:39:15,596
If I'm going to be forced
to watch television, may I smoke?

814
01:39:16,760 --> 01:39:18,796
Yes. Give him his cigarettes.

815
01:39:18,920 --> 01:39:22,356
It won't be the nicotine
that kills you, Mr Bond.

816
01:39:39,040 --> 01:39:41,474
Armed guards to control room.

817
01:39:55,800 --> 01:39:57,995
- Close the crater.
- Close crater!

818
01:39:58,120 --> 01:40:01,590
I shall look forward personally
to exterminating you, Mr Bond.

819
01:40:56,600 --> 01:40:58,272
Close the shutters.

820
01:41:06,440 --> 01:41:08,670
We are now impregnable.

821
01:41:08,800 --> 01:41:12,509
Interception takes place in eight minutes.
Nothing can prevent that.

822
01:42:37,720 --> 01:42:40,075
Impregnable?

823
01:42:40,200 --> 01:42:43,317
- Come with me, Mr Bond.
- Bird 1 to base. Locked on target.

824
01:42:43,440 --> 01:42:45,954
- Osato?
- Yes, Number One?

825
01:42:47,560 --> 01:42:49,551
Base calling Bird 1.

826
01:42:49,680 --> 01:42:52,831
You are to assume full control
of operation from now on.

827
01:42:52,960 --> 01:42:54,916
Seven minutes to interception.

828
01:42:55,040 --> 01:42:56,996
Roger, Base One.

829
01:42:57,680 --> 01:42:59,398
Houston, this is Hawaii.

830
01:42:59,520 --> 01:43:01,476
We have an unidentified object on scope.

831
01:43:01,600 --> 01:43:03,875
Order first alert. Arm all weapons.

832
01:43:04,000 --> 01:43:06,639
Interception will occur in six minutes.

833
01:43:13,320 --> 01:43:16,357
This is the price of failure, Mr Bond.

834
01:43:21,880 --> 01:43:23,836
Come on.

835
01:43:33,760 --> 01:43:35,876
Goodbye, Mr Bond.

836
01:43:45,960 --> 01:43:49,953
There's an exploder button in the
control room. We've got to get up there.

837
01:43:50,080 --> 01:43:52,036
Impossible. Too well defended.

838
01:43:57,640 --> 01:43:59,596
Evacuate the control!

839
01:44:00,080 --> 01:44:01,479
Evacuate the control!

840
01:44:20,560 --> 01:44:24,678
Control room technicians.
There must be another way up there.

841
01:44:35,920 --> 01:44:38,070
Give me cover till I get to the staircase.

842
01:46:18,320 --> 01:46:20,276
Bon appétit.

843
01:46:35,880 --> 01:46:38,599
Closing fast on our vehicle.
Orbit identical.

844
01:46:39,240 --> 01:46:42,550
All units stand by for codeword.
Codeword is imminent.

845
01:46:42,680 --> 01:46:45,353
I repeat, closing fast on our vehicle.

846
01:47:14,480 --> 01:47:16,232
It's blown up! The enemy!

847
01:47:16,360 --> 01:47:18,669
I repeat, the enemy has blown up.

848
01:47:18,800 --> 01:47:21,189
All units will return to first alert.

849
01:47:21,320 --> 01:47:24,517
Codeword is not -
I say again, not - imminent.

850
01:47:27,720 --> 01:47:29,597
Tiger,

851
01:47:29,720 --> 01:47:30,948
we've done it.

852
01:47:49,720 --> 01:47:51,995
Down the tunnel!

853
01:49:10,360 --> 01:49:12,316
Steady.

854
01:49:26,960 --> 01:49:29,520
Now... about that honeymoon.

855
01:49:29,640 --> 01:49:31,596
Why not?

856
01:49:31,720 --> 01:49:33,870
But they'll never let you stay.

857
01:49:35,040 --> 01:49:36,996
But they'll never find us.

858
01:50:02,480 --> 01:50:05,950
- Dinghy's on board, sir.
- Tell him to come below and report.

859
01:50:06,080 --> 01:50:08,389
It'll be a pleasure, sir.

860
01:51:41,000 --> 01:51:42,956
Subtitles by Visiontext

